HEADWORD: Puddening
<hw>Pud"den*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably fr.
<ets>pudden</ets>, for <ets>pudding</ets>, in allusion to its
softness.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A quantity of
rope-yarn, or the like, placed, as a fender, on the bow of a boat.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A bunch of soft material to prevent chafing between
spars, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pudder</ent>⟦br⟧
